The paper deals with the recovery of a low-rank matrix from a minimal number of measurements, which is a problem that falls under the category of compressed sensing (cs). The use of the restricted isometry property (RIP) also suggests that the paper may belong to the information theory (IT) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of nuclear-norm minimization, which is a common technique in machine learning (LG) and computer vision (CV) for low-rank matrix recovery. The extension of the error bounds to full-rank matrices suggests that the paper may also belong to the numerical analysis (NA) sub-category. Lastly, the paper discusses the use of oracle bounds, which is a topic that falls under the statistical inference (SI) sub-category.
